A sleek silver laptop sits open on a minimalist wooden desk, its screen glowing with reflected light from a large window. Surrounding the laptop in careful arrangement: a ceramic cup of black coffee with steam rising, a small potted succulent, and a coiled USB-C cable. The desk surface shows subtle scratches and wear marks from years of use. In the soft morning light streaming through sheer curtains, dust particles float visibly in the air. The laptop screen displays an abstract pattern of colorful terminal windows and code editors, blurred just enough to be unreadable. A single ethernet cable snakes off the edge of the desk. The scene conveys the quiet anticipation of a fresh start, the ritual of setting up a new creative workspace. Photorealistic style with shallow depth of field, warm natural lighting, shot from a slightly elevated three-quarter angle.